      <p>
A yo-yo has mass m and rotational inertia \(I\). A light thin string is wrapped around the central part of the yo-yo that has radius \(r\). The string is attached to the ceiling as shown. The yo-yo is released from rest and begins to descend as the string unwraps. The positive "y" direction is downward, as indicated by the arrow on the diagram.
</p>
